\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating enum usage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether enum constants are functional features. They serve as fields and can represent a fixed Arquillian resource, but ArquillianResource seems designed for injection fields rather than enum constants. That makes me wonder if using enum constants for this purpose is a bit unnatural. I should probably consider how this aligns or diverges from the intended use of ArquillianResource. It's intriguing to ponder the implications involved!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering annotation implementation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether a class can implement an annotation interface, and it seems allowed. However, implementing it manually requires the equals/hashCode methods, which leads me to consider how it tests the interface contract and the existing equality standards for annotations. I should explore the issue patterns since the goal is to enhance tests for metadata coverage. Existing tests rely on reflection, but I want to add functional usage to trigger native code. I'll compile carefully, considering new features like `@ArquillianResource` for lambda parameter annotations. This is functional and not already covered by reflection, which is great!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring lambda annotations**\\n\\nI’m looking at a syntax example where I'm using an annotation on a lambda parameter, specifically with the target set to PARAMETER. Yes, I can do this if I'm using explicit types or var. Invoking the callback reads well since it utilizes the annotation public API without relying on reflection. That's a great feature! I wonder if this aligns with Arquillian's intentions from 2015 and whether a formal parameter includes lambda in its considerations. It feels like a different logic flow, which is interesting!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pKeZA7QMvmEueEKuSudFCgMR|fc_0f185721c1b445330169f3dfc909788193bf067d68dbfb3ba7", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_test/arquillian_test_api/Arquillian_test_apiTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void constructorParametersCanDeclareArquillianResources() throws Exception {\n        Constructor<ResourceConsumer> constructor = ResourceConsumer.class.getDeclaredConstructor(Object.class, URL.class);\n        Parameter defaultParameter = constructor.getParameters()[0];\n        Parameter urlParameter = constructor.getParameters()[1];\n\n        ArquillianResource defaultResource = defaultParameter.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n        ArquillianResource urlResource = urlParameter.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n\n        assertThat(defaultResource).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(defaultResource.value()).isEqualTo(ArquillianResource.class);\n        assertThat(urlResource).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(urlResource.value()).isEqualTo(URL.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void annotationContractAllowsRuntimeLookupOnFieldsAndParametersOnly() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void constructorParametersCanDeclareArquillianResources() throws Exception {\n        Constructor<ResourceConsumer> constructor = ResourceConsumer.class.getDeclaredConstructor(Object.class, URL.class);\n        Parameter defaultParameter = constructor.getParameters()[0];\n        Parameter urlParameter = constructor.getParameters()[1];\n\n        ArquillianResource defaultResource = defaultParameter.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n        ArquillianResource urlResource = urlParameter.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n\n        assertThat(defaultResource).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(defaultResource.value()).isEqualTo(ArquillianResource.class);\n        assertThat(urlResource).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(urlResource.value()).isEqualTo(URL.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void lambdaCallbackParametersCanDeclareArquillianResources() throws Exception {\n        ResourceUrlFormatter formatter = (@ArquillianResource(URL.class) URL resourceUrl) -> resourceUrl.toExternalForm();\n        URL resourceUrl = URI.create(\"https://arquillian.example/deployments/app\").toURL();\n\n        assertThat(formatter.format(resourceUrl)).isEqualTo(\"https://arquillian.example/deployments/app\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void annotationContractAllowsRuntimeLookupOnFieldsAndParametersOnly() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static ArquillianResource annotationOnField(String fieldName) throws Exception {\n        Field field = ResourceConsumer.class.getDeclaredField(fieldName);\n        return field.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceConsumer {\n", "newText": "    private static ArquillianResource annotationOnField(String fieldName) throws Exception {\n        Field field = ResourceConsumer.class.getDeclaredField(fieldName);\n        return field.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface ResourceUrlFormatter {\n        String format(URL resourceUrl);\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceConsumer {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 757, "output": 2663, "cacheRead": 10240, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 13660, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777590186333, "responseId": "resp_0f185721c1b445330169f3dfab0af48193bab4a881c0c0dcac"}}
